text: The 46th District of the Iowa Senate is located in eastern Iowa, and is currently composed of Muscatine and Scott Counties. ==Current elected officials== Mark Lofgren is the senator currently representing the 46th District. The area of the 46th District contains two Iowa House of Representatives districts: *The 91st District (represented by Gary Carlson) *The 92nd District (represented by Ross Paustian) The district is also located in Iowa's 2nd congressional district, which is represented by David Loebsack. ==Past senators== The district has previously been represented by: *Delbert W. Floy, 1965–1966 *Merle W. Hagedorn, 1967–1968 *J. Leslie Leonard, 1969–1970 *Charles Peter Miller, 1971–1972 *Bass Van Gilst, 1973–1982 *James E. Briles, 1983–1984 *Leonard Boswell, 1985–1992 *Patty Judge, 1993–1998 *John Judge, 1999–2000 *Paul McKinley, 2001–2002 *Gene Fraise, 2003–2012 *Chris Brase, 2013–2016 *Mark Lofgren, 2017–present ==References== 46
